<subSubSection id="FDAA651F06392E75FF48FDB9FF00240A" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B50F369406392E75FF48FDB9FF00240A" blockId="19.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606392E75FF48FDB9FED125FA" bold="true" box="[199,315,150,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706392E75FECEFDB9FD8A25FA" authorityName="De Man" authorityYear="1888" box="[321,608,150,176]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilgendorfi">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606392E75FECEFDB9FD8A25FA" box="[321,608,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Cryptodromia hilgendorfi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described and figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506392E75FC3FFDB8FBBF25FA" author="McLay C. L." box="[944,1109,150,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="111 - 251" refId="ref27774" refString="McLay C. L. (1993) Crustacea Decapoda: the sponge crabs (Dromiidae) of New Caledonia and the Philippines with a review of the genera. In: Crosnier, A. (Ed.), Resultats des campagnes MUSORSTOM, volume 10. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 156, 111 - 251" type="journal article" year="1993">McLay (1993)</bibRefCitation>
. This species was reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506392E75FF18FD95FE11259E" author="Campbell, B. M. &amp; Stephenson, W." box="[151,507,186,212]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="235 - 301" refId="ref25152" refString="Campbell, B. M. &amp; Stephenson, W. (1970) The sublittoral Brachyura (Crustacea: Decapoda) of Moreton Bay. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 15, 235 - 301." type="journal article" year="1970">Campbell &amp; Stephenson (1970)</bibRefCitation>
from Moreton 
<collectingRegion id="7774F87606392E75FD28FD94FD3F259F" box="[679,725,187,213]" country="Somalia" name="Bay" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Bay</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="7774F87606392E75FD6EFD95FC82259E" box="[737,872,186,212]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Queensland</collectingRegion>
, where it was the subject of a detailed study about its population biology, settlement and use of sponges and ascidians for concealment (
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506392E75FBDAFDF1FB0025B2" author="McLay, C. L." box="[1109,1258,222,248]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="317 - 326" refId="ref27592" refString="McLay, C. L. (1982) Population biology of the sponge crab Cryptodromia hilgendorfi (Dromiacea) in Moreton Bay, Queensland, Australia. Marine Biology, 70, 317 - 326. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00396850" type="journal article" year="1982">McLay 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506392E75FB7AFDF1FADB25B2" author="McLay, C. L." box="[1269,1329,222,248]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="17 - 32" refId="ref27640" refString="McLay, C. L. (1983) Dispersal and use of sponges and ascidians as camouflage by Cryptodromia hilgendorfi (Brachyura: Dromiacea). Marine Biology, 76, 17 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00393051" type="journal article" year="1983">1983</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706392E75FACAFDF0FE832456" authorityName="De Man" authorityYear="1888" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilgendorfi">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606392E75FACAFDF0FE832456" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Cryptodromia hilgendorfi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains the only dromiid whose reproductive biology and growth pattern have been investigated to date.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FDAA651F06392E75FF48FC65FEB324E7" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B50F369406392E75FF48FC65FEB324E7" blockId="19.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606392E75FF48FC65FE8B242E" bold="true" box="[199,353,330,356]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Distribution.</emphasis>
Indo-West Pacific including Red Sea to Funafuti Atoll, Philippine Ids, 
<collectingCountry id="CDA7760406392E75FB3AFC64FA82242E" box="[1205,1384,330,357]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
and Queensland. The present material is the first to be reported from Western Australia. Depth range for the species is intertidal to 
<quantity id="72489B7106392E75FEAFFCBDFEB324E7" box="[288,345,402,429]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" unit="m" value="88.0">88 m</quantity>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
